Profile?gid=rigorre>Rigorre</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Registered User</span><br>  Posts: 1<br> <font color=#00FFFF>(12/2/02 2:37:52 pm)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub6.ezboard.com/ftherathetravelagencyfrm15.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=887.topic>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title>   Severlious Rot</span><hr size=1> I have not been asked to come here by my guild, nor am I an official representative \ speaker of said guild...<br>
<br>
I just have a question.  <br>
<br>
Champions of Norrath is currently second in line for Severlious on the rotation behind LoM.  We've been second in line for Severlious for several spawns now ...because LoM keeps 'passing' to allow other guilds the chance to be placed on the Rot.  This is NOT IN ANY WAY A FLAME to LoM!  I commend them on allowing the younger guilds their chances.<br>
<br>
However ...something seems to be wrong with the rule as I understand it.  LoM 'passes' their rotation to a younger guild, yet doesn't lose their place in line, correct?  This means that LoM can pretty much 'pass' their rot forever?  ...effectively keeping those guilds who are on the rot their fair chance?  As near as I can see, LoM will always be 'next on the rot'...<br>
<br>
In all fairness, we have posted on the LoM guild forums prior to the 11/30 spawn asking if we could push ahead of LoM on the rotation, since they seem to be passing anyways, but were told that they would be 'taking Severlious down as soons as they see him up' ...and then they passed again.<br>
<br>
I'm new to the inner workings of the server guild relationships and this board, so if you want to flame, flame away ...but I do respect the policies here.  I do not have now, nor ever have held any ill will towards LoM.  I just wanted to clarify the rotation rule for my own quest for knowledge. <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#222222><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub6.ezboard.com/btherathetravelagency.showUserPublicProfile?gid=dovelyngoldenheart>Dovelyn Goldenheart</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Registered User</span><br>  Posts: 653<br> <font color=#00FFFF>(12/2/02 3:15:26 pm)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub6.ezboard.com/ftherathetravelagencyfrm15.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=887.topic&index=1>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title>   Re: Severlious Rot</span><hr size=1> Sounds like they're not 'passing', but rather, letting another guild have a shot getting on the rot.  Maybe it would be good form for a rotation guild to only do that once on their turn, though, so that the next guild in line isn't waiting a month.  You don't want to penalize a guild for being nice, but at the same time, you want to respect your other rotation guilds. <p><!--EZCODE LINK START--><a href="http://www.magelo.com/eq_view_profile.html?num=26803" target="top"><!--EZCODE IMAGE START--><img src="http://home.austin.rr.com/fianna/DoveSig.jpg" style="border:0;"/><!--EZCODE IMAGE END--></a><!--EZCODE LINK END--></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#000000><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub6.ezboard.com/btherathetravelagency.showUserPublicProfile?gid=hutterr>Hutterr</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Fallen Shadows</span><br>  Posts: 100<br> <font color=#00FFFF>(12/2/02 3:20:53 pm)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub6.ezboard.com/ftherathetravelagencyfrm15.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=887.topic&index=2>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title>   Re: Severlious Rot</span><hr size=1> I agree wholeheartedly. I commend LoM for allowing younger guilds their chance, but multiple allowances negates the purpose of the rot (that being that no one guild/entity etc. can dictate who gets what spawns when). <br>
<br>
If one guild has the turn and can allow unlimited other guilds chances and take it when they want, then in all practicality, they control the spwan for the whole server.<br>
<br>
This is something that perhaps should be discussed in rep forums, that a guild is only allowed to offer 2 other guilds &quot;in on&quot; their turn. <br>
 <p>Hutterr Verbruggen<br>
<br>
57 Druid<br>
<br>
Fallen Shadows</p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#222222><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub6.ezboard.com/btherathetravelagency.showUserPublicProfile?gid=ghalidsoulsaver>Ghalid Soulsaver</A>&nbsp; <IMG HEIGHT=10 WIDTH=10 SRC="http://personal.bhm.bellsouth.net/bhm/w/i/wilsonua/pstgif.gif" BORDER=0></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Legend of Marr</span><br>  Posts: 142<br> <font color=#00FFFF>(12/2/02 3:23:45 pm)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub6.ezboard.com/ftherathetravelagencyfrm15.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=887.topic&index=3>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title>   Re: Severlious Rot</span><hr size=1> We have actually only allowed one guild (Clan Bashmed) to go ahead of us.  The others (Clan X and Evolutia Draconis) found Sev up before us, then either asked us if they could take him or proceeded to do so to get on the rotation.  We either race and be the Big Bad Uber Guild stomping on the little guild...or we be fair and say go for it..you guys found him up.  <br>
<br>
We are trying to watch for him as best we can.  Sev the past 2 spawns has spawned 2 and 1 day earlier then the projected time on the Calendar.  We do check before those days though as well.  I often take my roomate's druid but have not found him.<br>
<br>
Yes we want Sev and are not passing on him in any means.  We are being fair to other guilds that do find him that are not on the rotation.<br>
<br>
Ghalid Soulsaver<br>
Co-Leader Legend of Marr<br>
<br>
 <p></p><i>Edited by: <A HREF=http://pub6.ezboard.com/btherathetravelagency.showUserPublicProfile?gid=ghalidsoulsaver>Ghalid Soulsaver</A>&nbsp; <IMG HEIGHT=10 WIDTH=10 SRC="http://personal.bhm.bellsouth.net/bhm/w/i/wilsonua/pstgif.gif" BORDER=0> at: 12/2/02 3:27:00 pm<br></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#000000><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub6.ezboard.com/btherathetravelagency.showUserPublicProfile?gid=pontsuboy>Pontsuboy</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Registered User</span><br>  Posts: 1<br> <font color=#00FFFF>(12/2/02 3:59:09 pm)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub6.ezboard.com/ftherathetravelagencyfrm15.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=887.topic&index=4>Reply</a>   <BR><img src=http://members.home.com/pontsuboy/johnf.jpg WIDTH=60 HEIGHT=60></td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title>   Re: Severlious Rot</span><hr size=1> Although being fair to guilds that find a rot mob up is fine, being on rotation also connotes a bit of responsibility to aggressively pursue mobX.  This particular mob is the worst on the rot - it's an epic bottleneck and there are now 23 guilds on rotation.  By not aggressively pursuing their turn on Severlious, a guild causes the guilds behind them to wait indefinitely.  How is it that on successive turns on rotation, LoM has let three guilds beat them to Severlious?  It sounds like a matter of priority over.  We all know that there is a random element to spawn times for these mobs swinging to both early and late.  This particular mob is now, for all intents and purposes, a twice a year shot for guilds.  SOE/VI has ignored the mountains of feedback concerning this ever-increasing bottleneck.  It comes down to the player community to excercise some level of responsibility.<br>
<br>
I agree with the two chance and pass suggestion.  It will promote the type of aggressiveness that a guild on rotation *should* have while still leaving room for situations that make it impossible to take turns on rot.<br>
<br>
Tupic_CoN <p></p><i>Edited by: <A HREF=http://pub6.ezboard.com/btherathetravelagency.showUserPublicProfile?gid=pontsuboy>Pontsuboy</A> at: 12/2/02 4:03:26 pm<br></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#222222><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub6.ezboard.com/btherathetravelagency.showUserPublicProfile?gid=aandiian>Aandiian</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Registered User</span><br>  Posts: 74<br> <font color=#00FFFF>(12/2/02 4:41:29 pm)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub6.ezboard.com/ftherathetravelagencyfrm15.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=887.topic&index=5>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title>   Re: Severlious Rot</span><hr size=1> .. Why is it so hard to read what they already said in response .. Sev spawned days early, on 2 occasions.  With the current status of the sev rotation, each guild will maybe get 2-3 turns a year .. if more guilds do not get on to the rotation.  <br>
<br>
What has LoM done wrong?  They were asked once for a chance at Sev, and they allowed it, because they did not have the force on at the time, and it was very nice of them to let that guild have a shot to get on the rotation.  The next two times, Sev spawned 1-2 days earlier than he was supposed to.<br>
<br>
I would think that after you (tupic) posted on lom's board asking them to pass so you can get your epic that you have been waiting forever for, and getting a response.. that you would not need to post about it again, here. /shrug.<br>
<br>
Aandiian <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#000000><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title><A HREF="http://www.ezboard.com/promotions/csc.html" TARGET="_blank" ><IMG SRC="http://www.ezboard.com/image/cscicon3.gif" WIDTH="20" HEIGHT="20" BORDER="0" align="absmiddle"></A> <A HREF=http://pub6.ezboard.com/btherathetravelagency.showUserPublicProfile?gid=daiaspiritlight>Daia Spiritlight</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Evolutia Draconis</span><br>  Posts: 59<br> <font color=#00FFFF>(12/2/02 4:44:57 pm)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub6.ezboard.com/ftherathetravelagencyfrm15.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=887.topic&index=6>Reply</a>    <br>ezSupporter<br> </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title>   Severilous Rot(ation)</span><hr size=1> I added the coda in the title because when I first saw this I jumped in my seat wondering how the mob could have respawned and rotted already when we'd just killed him Saturday morning. =)<br>
<br>
Just to confirm what Ghalid reported about this most recent spawn.  EvD did not &quot;prearrange&quot; with LoM to take Sev down and LoM did not formally &quot;pass&quot; to Evolutia Draconis.  Our guild spies found Severilous up a day early at an extremely early hour on Saturday morning (around 7:30 AM Pacific) -- most LoM were not even online at the time from what my /who's could discern.  Yet since we were scheduled to be up in Sky starting at 9:00 AM, a killing force of our members *was* online.  We decided we simply couldn't pass up the rare-for-us opportunity.  <br>
<br>
I know for a fact that LoM was intending to take Sev on their turn (and surmise that they probably would *not* have agreed to wait), because on Saturday night, an LoM member who is close friends with my husband but had not yet heard that EvD had taken Severilious was jumping up and down with chat excitement over the fact that LoM was finally again up for Sev the next day and with luck the green meanie would finally drop a warrior scale for him.  Imagine his surprise <!--EZCODE EMOTICON START ;) --><img src=http://www.ezboard.com/images/emoticons/wink.gif ALT=";)"><!--EZCODE EMOTICON END--> <br>
<br>
Given that, I simply cannot conclude that LoM was not &quot;vigilent&quot; or &quot;dropped the ball&quot; on this particular turn.  Obviously I know nothing about the others but I would hate to have a situation where LoM or any other guild in their situation gets fussed at solely because they did not immediately buffalo over us with whatever forces they had online (not many, believe me -- I was checking, much as I love you, LoM &lt;giggle&gt;) solely because they heard that EvD had found Sev up and was mobilizing, just to avoid a claim that they were &quot;passing too much&quot; without &quot;regard&quot; for the guilds coming behind them.  In the end the vigilence to kill the mob before its scheduled spawn time should not have to rest *too* much with those already on rotation - after all they have proven themselves and rightfully have earned the right to the &quot;24 hour leisure&quot; that the rotation creates. The vigilence fairly rests with guilds like mine who are just now &quot;up and coming&quot;, for us to seize unexpected opportunities like the one we seized on Saturday unless we do pre-arrange something with the rotation guild (BTW I like the idea of having a maximum limit of 1 or 2 formal &quot;arrangements&quot; per turn).  After all, EvD might have failed at Sev or LoM might have spotted him first.  In that event, this entire thread would have been moot.<br>
<br>
I empathize with the frustration of guilds who suddenly find themselves &quot;bumped&quot; because someone took advantage of an unexpected spawn timer shift on the turn of the guild before them.  But I'm not sure what you can do about that, other than to eliminate the rotation altogether or have a requirement that guilds start camping their anticipated spawns days earlier than scheduled.  If that happens, it would guarantee that &quot;up and coming guilds&quot; would never have a shot, and probably guarantee that some guilds who are not 24-7 guilds would be tossed from the rotation because they simply do not have the membership for that type of hypervigilence.  While that's convenient definitely -- nobody likes to wait, after all -- it seems to defeat the spirit of the rotations to begin with.<br>
<br>
Since I didn't run the above by my guild first, all the above is just Daia and not EvD. <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#222222><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub6.ezboard.com/btherathetravelagency.showUserPublicProfile?gid=rigorre>Rigorre</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Registered User</span><br>  Posts: 2<br> <font color=#00FFFF>(12/2/02 5:35:22 pm)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub6.ezboard.com/ftherathetravelagencyfrm15.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=887.topic&index=7>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title>   Re: Severilous Rot(ation)</span><hr size=1> First of all, Aandiian, I'm not Tupic ...I'm Rigorre ...Rigorre Morrtisse, Necromancer, Champions of Norrath ...at your service.  If you ever call me by the name of that lazy, good for nuthin' Troll again, I will have no choice but to cut out your tongue, chop off all of your fingers, and gouge your eyes out with an ice pick.  <!--EZCODE EMOTICON START :) --><img src=http://www.ezboard.com/images/emoticons/smile.gif ALT=":)"><!--EZCODE EMOTICON END--> <br>
<br>
I do not have a warrior character, nor do I play one on TV.  I only tolerate the class to share the same air I breathe because, at one time or another, they may be needed for sacrifice.  It is far more of a luxury and honor than I give those vile Paladins and Druids.<br>
<br>
I am merely asking questions here ...it is not my desire to use an accusatory tone against LoM.  I am certain they have behaved honorably in this situation .  <br>
<br>
So far, some good ideas are forming from my little insignificant post.  I like the &quot;2 chances and your out&quot; idea, but truthfully I couldn't argue a case for it with my limited knowledge of how things are done.  Would be interested in hearing Roggulbuk's thoughts on it, however, as I've lurked here long enough to respect his opinion.<br>
<br>
----<br>
Vile-ly Yours,<br>
 <br>
Rigorre Morrtisse<br>
Champions of Norrath <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#000000><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub6.ezboard.com/btherathetravelagency.showUserPublicProfile?gid=pontsuboy>Pontsuboy</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Registered User</span><br>  Posts: 2<br> <font color=#00FFFF>(12/2/02 5:43:53 pm)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub6.ezboard.com/ftherathetravelagencyfrm15.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=887.topic&index=8>Reply</a>   <BR><img src=http://members.home.com/pontsuboy/johnf.jpg WIDTH=60 HEIGHT=60></td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title>   Re: Severilous Rot(ation)</span><hr size=1> <!--EZCODE AUTOLINK START--><a href="http://www.legendofmarr.com/board/viewtopic.php?t=1875">www.legendofmarr.com/boar...php?t=1875</a><!--EZCODE AUTOLINK END--><br>
<br>
Sure Aand, I asked if LoM was taking their turn or if not please pass.  Sure I find it frustrating that this particular guild has on two consecutive rotations allowed at least three other guilds to jump in (allowed due to kindness or getting beaten).  After Ghalid's response, I expected LoM to be ready to jump Sev.  Sure Sev spawned a day early (I think I already mentioned the random aspect of such mobs).  Why would someone then question vigilence when we see the same result of delay repeatedly?<br>
<br>
The question *is* vigilance as Daia mentioned.  EvD was vigilant enough to watch for their opportunity as were, what you seem to be claiming, five other guilds.  If mobX is not a priority, simply pass.  If mobX is a priority, take the mob down.  How hard is that?  <br>
<br>
This isn't the first post on Severlious frustration.  This mob is a bottleneck, arguably the worst now since Ragefire was addressed.  Hell, if I had the time I'd personally camp EJ night and day and call your members at home just like the old Ragefire camps to help you get your turn.  I'm sure their are other folks waiting just as impatiently and watching with forlorn expressions as they see the rotation for Sev growing and their wait increasing.  Perhaps the rotation cap proposal should be enacted - you may only belong to X number of rotations - would that help to prioritize?<br>
<br>
